OmniPlanner is a free, open-source life planning app designed to reduce context switching and protect attention.
Instead of forcing people to jump between email, calendar, weekly planning, habits, alarms, and study timers, it brings those systems into one calm workspace built for deliberate living.

The product is built around a simple idea: discipline should not depend on expensive subscriptions, manipulative engagement design, or handing your life over to invasive platforms. Users can plan long-term goals, break them into weekly priorities, schedule them into real time, and act on them without leaving the app and getting pulled into external distractions.

AI exists as an optional tool, not the product itself. It can help with planning or drafting when the user wants it, but it is never the center of the experience. The core value is focus, structure, and ownership.

The app is intended to be sustainable through donations and ethical sponsorships, not ads, data extraction, or paywalls around self-discipline. The goal is to build a trusted digital environment where personal discipline is accessible, privacy-respecting, and genuinely user-first.
